    .provide-storage
      :markdown
        There is an npm package available for building custom remoteStorage servers, called
        [remotestorage-server](https://www.npmjs.org/package/remotestorage-server). It is
        the basis of the [starter-kit](https://github.com/remotestorage/starter-kit#remotestorage-starter-kit) and
        will be updated whenever new versions of the spec come out.

        To add remoteStorage support to your online storage product, please check out our
        [forum category](http://community.remotestorage.io/category/server-development) 
        and follow our latest IETF Internet Draft:
        [draft-dejong-remotestorage-03](http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-dejong-remotestorage-03).

        All existing providers are still using one of the previous two versions, [draft-dejong-remotestorage-01](http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-dejong-remotestorage-01) and [draft-dejong-remotestorage-02](http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-dejong-remotestorage-02), but historical versions [2010.12, 2011.04, 2011.12, 2012.04, and draft-dejong-remotestorage-00](https://github.com/remotestorage/spec/) are now deprecated.

